column5: Well once again, we had a fab time up at Maskinonge Lodge.  Regan and Goldie are the best hosts and the cabins are great.  We arrived after a trip from hell where right off the bat, the passenger side window broke, so we had to keep stopping to put paper in it or it would keep sliding down, which sucks on the highway.  Then we got another flat (good thing we bought a new spare) and had to change it just before Barrie (which was a 3 hour drive just from Richmond Hill).   So, lets just say, the drive up was unpleasant and ended up being 6 hours instead of the usual 3 1/2 to 4 hrs.  Just as we were pulling into the camp, I saw the Sandhill Cranes I have been trying to get a picture of for a long time.  Paul stopped for me and I went running to get a picture, which of course scared them, so these were the best I could get as they took off.  IMG_6806 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6814 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6846 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6843 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr     Fishing was not as good as the weeds are still not up as high as normal.  But Paul did manage to get a nice 46" musky and my son got a few pike.    I got a few pike aswell, but as usual, the cameraman never gets any pics taken of themselves.  IMG_1454 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   I think he's happy in  this picture  IMG_1452 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  My son and his mini pike  IMG_1461 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   Another one a bit bigger, which we kept for the fish fry.  Thanks Patsy for doing the major work on that.  Ralphie loves when we catch fish  IMG_1465 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_7133 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr    We got a huge thunderstorm and barely made it back to camp.  It rolled in and gave us a good light show.  IMG_7284 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_7240 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr    Thought this cloud looked cool after the storm with the sun behind it  IMG_7288 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr    Some random shots  IMG_6889 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6863 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6857 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   Osprey fishing  IMG_7177 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_7077 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   A turtle I assume  IMG_7043 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6987 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr  IMG_6958 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   But, we had a great time and are already planning on going back up for the fall bite in September.  Could not have had better company than we had and can't wait to do it all again next year.   Thanks all for such a good time.  Thanks Regan and Goldie for the BBQ and for being such awesome camp owners.   I think your place is going to do well.  We will definitely be back.  Joey
Great shots as usual Joey and nice seeing you all again.  Oh yeah - and thanks for telling everyone that Paul's was two inches longer than mine
Great shots as usual Joey and nice seeing you all again.  Oh yeah - and thanks for telling everyone that Paul's was two inches longer than mine

nice report   great photos  but Paul caught the big one  sounds like tall tales to me

looks like the who's who of the OFC up there  great pics as usual, not enough Ralphie  shots though, to remind me of my old Boston (I know Ralphie isn't a Boston, but they look similar)

Very nice pics Joey, and that is a solid muskie that Paul caught! One of these years I will make it up to Nip...  Pete
